\c 12
\cl Romans 12
\cd Lessons of Christian virtues.
\p
\v 1 I beseech you, therefore, brethren, by the mercy of God, *that you present your bodies a living sacrifice, holy, pleasing to God, your reasonable service.
\p
\v 2 And be not conformed to this world: but be reformed in the newness of your mind: *that you may prove what is the good, and the acceptable, and the perfect will of God.
\p
\v 3 For I say, through the grace that is given me, to all that are among you, not to be more wise than it behoveth to be wise, but to be wise unto sobriety: *and according as God hath divided to every one the measure of faith.
\p
\v 4 For as in one body we have many members, but all the members have not the same office:
\p
\v 5 So we, being many, are one body in Christ, and every one, members one of another.
\p
\v 6 And having gifts different, according to the grace that is given us, whether prophecy, according to the proportion of faith,
\p
\v 7 Or ministry, in ministering: or he that teacheth, in doctrine,
\p
\v 8 He that exhorteth in exhorting; he that giveth with simplicity; he that ruleth with solicitude, he that sheweth mercy with cheerfulness.
\p
\v 9 Love without dissimulation. *Hating that which is evil, adhering to that which is good:
\p
\v 10 *Loving one another with brotherly love; in honour preventing one another:
\p
\v 11 In solicitude not slothful: in spirit fervent: serving the Lord:
\p
\v 12 Rejoicing in hope: patient in tribulation: instant in prayer:
\p
\v 13 Communicating to the necessities of the saints: *pursuing hospitality.
\p
\v 14 Bless them that persecute you: bless, and curse not.
\p
\v 15 Rejoice with them that rejoice, weep with them that weep:
\p
\v 16 Being of one mind one towards another: not high-minded: but condescending to the humble. Be not wise in your own conceits:
\p
\v 17 Rendering to no man evil for evil: *providing things good, not only in the sight of God, but also in the sight of all men.
\p
\v 18 *If it be possible, as much as is in you, have peace with all men.
\p
\v 19 *Revenge not yourselves, my dearly beloved: but give place to wrath, for it is written: **Revenge is mine, I will repay, saith the Lord.
\p
\v 20 *But if thy enemy be hungry, give him to eat: if he thirst, give him drink: for, doing this, thou shalt heap coals of fire on his head.
\p
\v 21 *Be not overcome by evil, but overcome evil by good.
